# EpigeneticDrift — State

**Version:** 0.2.0  
**Status:** 🟡 In Development  
**Last Updated:** 2025-03-15  

## Overview

EpigeneticDrift is a research and development project aimed at building a robust computational pipeline to detect, quantify, and visualize epigenetic drift in human genomic data. Epigenetic drift refers to age-related changes in DNA methylation patterns that accumulate over time and can serve as biomarkers for biological aging, disease risk, and environmental exposures. The project will produce an open-source pipeline, a curated reference database of age-related epigenetic markers, and an interactive visualization dashboard. The ultimate goal is to publish a peer-reviewed paper describing the methodology and initial findings.

