- **Phase 1 (Foundation) – In Progress**  
  - Project kickoff meeting held (2025-03-01)  
  - Initial repository structure created (2025-03-05)  
  - CONCEPT.md draft completed (2025-03-10) – pending final review  
- **Phase 2 (Core Development) – Not started**  
- **Phase 3 (Validation & Publication) – Not started**  

## Goals & Tasks

All tasks are prioritized as **P0** (critical), **P1** (important), or **P2** (nice-to-have). Each task has a single owner and clear dependencies.

### P0 – Foundation (Must complete before any other work)

| Task ID | Description | Owner | Dependencies | Estimated Effort | Success Criteria |
|---------|-------------|-------|--------------|------------------|-----------------|
| T0.1 | Finalize CONCEPT.md with detailed objectives, deliverables, success criteria, and ethical considerations. | Project Manager | None | 2 days | Document approved by PI and stakeholders. |
| T0.2 | Set up project repository structure (Git), including directories for code, data, docs, tests, and CI/CD configuration. | Lead Developer | None | 1 day | Repository operational, version control active, CI passes on push. |
| T0.3 | Define coding standards, contribution guidelines, and issue templates. | Lead Developer | T0.2 | 0.5 day | Guidelines documented in CONTRIBUTING.md. |
| T0.4 | Establish communication channels (Slack, weekly stand-ups, shared calendar). | Project Manager | None | 0.5 day | All team members invited and first stand-up scheduled. |

### P1 – Core Development (After P0 complete)

| Task ID | Description | Owner | Dependencies | Estimated Effort | Success Criteria |
|---------|-------------|-------|--------------|------------------|-----------------|
| T1.1 | Create a comprehensive TODO list covering algorithm development, database creation, and visualization. | Project Manager | T0.1 | 1 day | TODO.md approved by team. |
| T1.2 | Implement core algorithm for methylation pattern comparison (e.g., beta-value difference, smoothing, statistical testing). | Lead Developer | T0.2, T1.1 | 4 weeks | Algorithm passes unit tests on synthetic data; documented in code and design doc. |
| T1.3 | Develop data ingestion module to handle common methylation array formats (IDAT, CSV, BED). | Data Scientist | T0.2, T1.1 | 2 weeks | Module reads at least three public datasets without error. |
| T1.4 | Write unit tests for core algorithm and data ingestion (coverage ≥80%). | Lead Developer | T1.2, T1.3 | 1 week | Tests pass in CI; coverage report generated. |
| T1.5 | Set up continuous integration (GitHub Actions) for automated testing and linting. | Lead Developer | T0.2 | 1 day | CI runs on every PR; status badges in README. |

### P2 – Validation & Publication (After P1 complete)

| Task ID | Description | Owner | Dependencies | Estimated Effort | Success Criteria |
|---------|-------------|-------|--------------|------------------|-----------------|
| T2.1 | Build a reference database of age-related epigenetic markers (≥100 markers from literature and public repositories). | Data Scientist | T1.3 | 3 weeks | Database contains curated markers with metadata (gene, CpG, age association, PMID). |
| T2.2 | Validate pipeline on at least three independent public datasets (e.g., GEO, TCGA). | Lead Developer | T1.4, T2.1 | 4 weeks | Results reproduce known age associations; false discovery rate <0.05. |
| T2.3 | Develop interactive visualization dashboard for drift analysis (e.g., using Plotly/Dash or R Shiny). | Frontend Developer | T1.2, T2.1 | 3 weeks | Dashboard deployed, allows filtering by age, tissue, marker; reviewed by PI. |
| T2.4 | Write manuscript describing methodology and initial findings. | Principal Investigator | T2.2, T2.3 | 6 weeks | Draft submitted to internal review; target journal identified. |
| T2.5 | Prepare open-source release (documentation, examples, PyPI package). | Lead Developer | T2.2 | 2 weeks | Package installable via pip; README with quickstart; DOI assigned. |

## Dependencies

- **P0 tasks** have no external dependencies; they are the foundation.  
- **P1 tasks** depend on completion of all P0 tasks (T0.1–T0.4).  
- **P2 tasks** depend on completion of all P1 tasks (T1.1–T1.5).  
- No circular dependencies exist.  
- External dependencies: Public methylation datasets (GEO, TCGA) – access is free; no licensing issues.  

## Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|------------|--------|------------|
| Algorithm fails to detect known drift signals | Medium | High | Use synthetic data with known ground truth; test on multiple datasets; consult domain experts. |
| Data format incompatibility | Low | Medium | Build flexible ingestion module; support common formats; document required columns. |
| Team member availability changes | Medium | Medium | Cross-train tasks; maintain documentation; have backup owners. |
| Publication delay due to journal review | High | Low | Submit to preprint server (bioRxiv) immediately; target open-access journals. |
| Dashboard performance with large datasets | Low | Medium | Implement data aggregation and caching; test with 1000+ samples. |

